text: Bryan Rose (born 24 July 1943) is a New Zealand former long-distance running athlete who participated in the 1973 IAAF World Cross Country Championships, where he was a member of the Winning New Zealand team. Also competed in the 1974 Commonwealth Games in the 5,000 metres.
